                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="major" script="nasta_liq" medium="ink"> Written in a
                                clear black nasta‘līq hand. </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <decoDesc>
                            <summary>The initial folios for each tale feature delicately illuminated
                                opening headpieces, with four paintings inserted at a later
                                date.</summary>
                            <decoNote type="headpiece">Illuminated opening features a domed
                                scalloped half-cloud-collar surmounting a rectangle below,
                                containing a blank gilt horizontal cartouche and finials with
                                infilled floral scrollwork set against an ultramarine
                                ground.</decoNote>
                            <decoNote type="illustration">
                                <list rend="numbered">
                                    <item n="1"><title>Mi‘rāj scene</title> from the
                                            <title>Iskandarnāmah</title><lb/>
                                        <desc>Prophet Muḥammad ascends to heaven on the composite
                                            mythical creature, al-Burāq</desc><lb/>
                                        <dimensions type="illustration" unit="mm">
                                            <height>120</height>
                                            <width>90</width>
                                        </dimensions>
                                    </item>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <item n="2"><title>Scribe seated outdoors</title>, possibly
