                    <history>
                        <origin>Probably completed in the <origPlace type="empire"
                                ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/6005089" key="place_6005089"
                                >Safavid Empire</origPlace> undated, but probably <origDate
                                cert="medium" calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="1500" notAfter="1600"
                                >16th century CE</origDate>. </origin>
                        <provenance>While the circumstances under which this volume arrived in
                            Britain remains unclear, collector <persName role="fmo col dno"
                                ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/77114097" key="person_77114097">Robert
                                Edward Hart (1878-1946)</persName> acquired it from an unidentified
                            source.</provenance>
                        <acquisition>Bequeathed to the <orgName role="rpo"
                                ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/144365237">Blackburn Museum and Art
                                Gallery</orgName>, <placeName key="place_7027442"
                                ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7027442">Blackburn,
                                Lancashire</placeName>, after the death of <persName
                                role="fmo col dno" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/77114097"
                                key="person_77114097">Robert Edward Hart (1878-1946)</persName> in
                                <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1946">1946</date>.</acquisition>
                    </history>
